Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array â€” Short Notes
Problem Essence

Array is sorted

Remove duplicates in-place

Keep unique elements at the start

Return count of unique elements k

Ignore elements after index k-1

Core Idea

Use two pointers

One pointer reads (i)

One pointer writes (k)

Overwrite duplicates instead of deleting

Algorithm

First element is always unique â†’ set k = 1

Loop from index 1 to end

If nums[i] != nums[i-1]

Write nums[i] at nums[k]

Increment k

Return k

Code (LeetCode format)
class Solution:
    def removeDuplicates(self, nums):
        if not nums:
            return 0

        k = 1
        for i in range(1, len(nums)):
            if nums[i] != nums[i - 1]:
                nums[k] = nums[i]
                k += 1
        return k

Example

Input:

[0,0,1,1,2,2,3]


Output:

k = 4
nums = [0,1,2,3,_,_,_]

Key Topics Used

Lists & indexing

For loop

If condition

Two pointers

In-place array modification

Sorted array property

Time & Space

Time: O(n)

Space: O(1)

